{
  "schema_version": 2,
  "comment": [
    "Per-benchmark build contract for the CAE difftest suite.",
    "",
    "Tier-1 (committed in-tree microbenchmarks): each benchmark produces",
    "two ELF variants built from the same source:",
    "  variants.qemu -> linked at 0x80000000 for qemu-system-riscv64 -bios,",
    "                    exits via ebreak + wfi halt loop",
    "  variants.se   -> linked at 0x00010000 for gem5 SE mode, exits via",
    "                    ecall (syscall 93)",
    "The Makefile passes -DGEM5_SE to select the SE exit path in bench.S.",
    "run-gem5.py picks the 'se' variant; run-cae.py picks the 'qemu'",
    "variant. sha256 is recorded per variant so drift in either build",
    "is caught before simulation starts.",
    "",
    "Tier-2 (host-provided release-gate binaries): entries reference",
    "binaries staged by the operator under $CAE_TIER2_BINARIES_DIR",
    "(default ~/cae-ready-to-run/). tier2_binary_relpath is relative to",
    "that directory; sha256 is pinned by the operator once staged. Until",
    "staged, sha256='PENDING_OPERATOR_STAGING' and the entry is tagged",
    "gated: false; run-xs-suite.sh --tier 2 is responsible for the final",
    "sha256 check at suite run time and for failing closed when a tier-2",
    "binary is missing (tier-1 runs remain unaffected).",
    "",
    "Per-benchmark metadata (every tier):",
    "  tier                : 1 (committed) or 2 (host-provided)",
    "  isa_subset          : rv64gc | rv64gcb | rv64gc_zifencei (etc.)",
    "  uses                : list of [scalar|fp|amo|rvv]; workloads",
    "                        touching RVV are carried here but tagged",
    "                        gated: false until trace v2 lands (AC-K-1.1)",
    "  frontend_sensitive  : true when the benchmark's IPC depends on the",
    "                        frontend (BPred / I-cache) to a degree that",
    "                        makes it ineligible for the M3' KPI gate and",
    "                        eligible only at M4' (AC-K-3.3 / AC-K-4)",
    "  reset_pc            : architectural reset / entry PC (CAE virt and",
    "                        XS baremetal baselines both reset at",
    "                        0x80000000); tier-2 entries declare this",
    "                        explicitly because they bypass variants.",
    "  gated               : whether the benchmark participates in",
    "                        ci-gate.py / diff.py aggregation in the",
    "                        current revision"
  ],
